{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1142,"text":"Ten years ago,"},{"time":2318,"text":"I had my first exhibition here."},{"time":4638,"text":"I had no idea if it would work\nor was at all possible,"},{"time":8678,"text":"but with a few small steps\nand a very steep learning curve,"},{"time":12115,"text":"I made my first sculpture,\ncalled \"The Lost Correspondent.\""},{"time":16406,"text":"Teaming up with a marine biologist\nand a local dive center,"},{"time":19847,"text":"I submerged the work\noff the coast of Grenada,"},{"time":22540,"text":"in an area decimated by Hurricane Ivan."},{"time":25957,"text":"And then this incredible thing happened."},{"time":28554,"text":"It transformed."},{"time":31675,"text":"One sculpture became two."},{"time":34955,"text":"Two quickly became 26."},{"time":38756,"text":"And before I knew it,"},{"time":39931,"text":"we had the world's first\nunderwater sculpture park."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44730,"text":"In 2009, I moved to Mexico\nand started by casting local fisherman."},{"time":50950,"text":"This grew to a small community,"},{"time":54218,"text":"to almost an entire movement of people\nin defense of the sea."},{"time":59228,"text":"And then finally, to an underwater museum,"},{"time":61945,"text":"with over 500 living sculptures."},{"time":66076,"text":"Gardening, it seems,\nis not just for greenhouses."},{"time":71375,"text":"We've since scaled up the designs:"},{"time":74041,"text":"\"Ocean Atlas,\" in the Bahamas,\nrising 16 feet up to the surface"},{"time":78175,"text":"and weighing over 40 tons,"},{"time":81825,"text":"to now currently in Lanzarote,"},{"time":83637,"text":"where I'm making\nan underwater botanical garden,"},{"time":86796,"text":"the first of its kind\nin the Atlantic Ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90834,"text":"Each project, we use materials\nand designs that help encourage life;"},{"time":95108,"text":"a long-lasting pH-neutral cement\nprovides a stable and permanent platform."},{"time":101398,"text":"It is textured to allow\ncoral polyps to attach."},{"time":105262,"text":"We position them down current\nfrom natural reefs"},{"time":108003,"text":"so that after spawning,\nthere's areas for them to settle."},{"time":113937,"text":"The formations are all configured\nso that they aggregate fish"},{"time":116859,"text":"on a really large scale."},{"time":120918,"text":"Even this VW Beetle\nhas an internal living habitat"},{"time":124503,"text":"to encourage crustaceans\nsuch as lobsters and sea urchins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130733,"text":"So why exhibit my work in the ocean?"},{"time":133497,"text":"Because honestly, it's really not easy."},{"time":136059,"text":"When you're in the middle of the sea\nunder a hundred-foot crane,"},{"time":139288,"text":"trying to lower eight tons\ndown to the sea floor,"},{"time":142407,"text":"you start to wonder whether I shouldn't\nhave taken up watercolor painting instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147385,"text":"But in the end, the results\nalways blow my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150122,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172791,"text":"The ocean is the most\nincredible exhibition space"},{"time":175735,"text":"an artist could ever wish for."},{"time":177430,"text":"You have amazing lighting effects\nchanging by the hour,"},{"time":180807,"text":"explosions of sand covering\nthe sculptures in a cloud of mystery,"},{"time":185148,"text":"a unique timeless quality"},{"time":187076,"text":"and the procession\nof inquisitive visitors,"},{"time":189140,"text":"each lending their own\nspecial touch to the site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191897,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219288,"text":"But over the years,"},{"time":220463,"text":"I've realized that the greatest\nthing about what we do,"},{"time":223846,"text":"the really humbling thing about the work,"},{"time":226369,"text":"is that as soon as we\nsubmerge the sculptures,"},{"time":228606,"text":"they're not ours anymore,"},{"time":230156,"text":"because as soon as we sink them,"},{"time":231728,"text":"the sculptures, they belong to the sea."},{"time":234013,"text":"As new reefs form, a new world\nliterally starts to evolve,"},{"time":238056,"text":"a world that continuously amazes me."},{"time":240750,"text":"It's a bit of a cliché,\nbut nothing man-made"},{"time":243242,"text":"can ever match the imagination of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246591,"text":"Sponges look like veins across the faces."},{"time":250478,"text":"Staghorn coral morphs the form."},{"time":254567,"text":"Fireworms scrawl white lines as they feed."},{"time":259557,"text":"Tunicates explode from the faces."},{"time":264597,"text":"Sea urchins crawl across\nthe bodies feeding at night."},{"time":270752,"text":"Coralline algae applies\na kind of purple paint."},{"time":275671,"text":"The deepest red I've ever seen\nin my life lives underwater."},{"time":282235,"text":"Gorgonian fans oscillate with the waves."},{"time":287002,"text":"Purple sponges breathe water like air."},{"time":291221,"text":"And grey angelfish\nglide silently overhead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296832,"text":"And the amazing response\nwe've had to these works"},{"time":299217,"text":"tells me that we've managed\nto plug into something really primal,"},{"time":303394,"text":"because it seems that these images\ntranslate across the world,"},{"time":307243,"text":"and that's made me focus\non my responsibility as an artist"},{"time":311108,"text":"and about what I'm trying to achieve."},{"time":313917,"text":"I'm standing here today on this boat\nin the middle of the ocean,"},{"time":317563,"text":"and this couldn't be a better place"},{"time":319310,"text":"to talk about the really,\nreally important effect of my work."},{"time":323461,"text":"Because as we all know,"},{"time":325145,"text":"our reefs are dying,\nand our oceans are in trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329160,"text":"So here's the thing:"},{"time":330454,"text":"the most used, searched and shared image"},{"time":333241,"text":"of all my work thus far is this."},{"time":337256,"text":"And I think this is for a reason,"},{"time":339430,"text":"or at least I hope it is."},{"time":341560,"text":"What I really hope is that people\nare beginning to understand"},{"time":344724,"text":"that when we think of the environment\nand the destruction of nature,"},{"time":348416,"text":"that we need to start thinking\nabout our oceans, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351684,"text":"Since building these sites,\nwe've seen some phenomenal"},{"time":354239,"text":"and unexpected results."},{"time":356260,"text":"Besides creating over 800 square meters\nof new habitats and living reef,"},{"time":361433,"text":"visitors to the marine park in Cancun\nnow divide half their time"},{"time":365481,"text":"between the museum and the natural reefs,"},{"time":368037,"text":"providing significant rest\nfor natural, overstressed areas."},{"time":372859,"text":"Visitors to \"Ocean Atlas\"\nin the Bahamas highlighted a leak"},{"time":376750,"text":"from a nearby oil refinery."},{"time":379251,"text":"The subsequent international media\nforced the local government"},{"time":382600,"text":"to pledge 10 million dollars\nin coastal cleanups."},{"time":386154,"text":"The sculpture park in Grenada\nwas instrumental"},{"time":388552,"text":"in the government designating a spot --\na marine-protected area."},{"time":392843,"text":"Entrance fees to the park\nnow help fund park rangers"},{"time":396226,"text":"to manage tourism and fishing quotas."},{"time":399293,"text":"The site was actually listed\nas a \"Wonder of the World\""},{"time":401925,"text":"by National Geographic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404297,"text":"So why are we all here today in this room?"},{"time":406901,"text":"What do we all have in common?"},{"time":409560,"text":"I think we all share a fear"},{"time":411219,"text":"that we don't protect our oceans enough."},{"time":413837,"text":"And one way of thinking about this"},{"time":415508,"text":"is that we don't regard\nour oceans as sacred,"},{"time":418877,"text":"and we should."},{"time":420572,"text":"When we see incredible places --"},{"time":422159,"text":"like the Himalayas\nor the La Sagrada Família,"},{"time":426121,"text":"or the Mona Lisa, even --"},{"time":427806,"text":"when we see these incredible\nplaces and things,"},{"time":430719,"text":"we understand their importance."},{"time":432788,"text":"We call them sacred,"},{"time":434202,"text":"and we do our best\nto cherish them, to protect them"},{"time":437883,"text":"and to keep them safe."},{"time":439970,"text":"But in order to do that,"},{"time":441209,"text":"we are the ones that have\nto assign that value;"},{"time":444563,"text":"otherwise, it will be desecrated"},{"time":446120,"text":"by someone who doesn't\nunderstand that value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449549,"text":"So I want to finish up tonight\nby talking about sacred things."},{"time":453408,"text":"When we were naming the site in Cancun,"},{"time":455586,"text":"we named it a museum for a very\nimportant and simple reason:"},{"time":459928,"text":"museums are places of preservation,"},{"time":462379,"text":"of conservation and of education."},{"time":465524,"text":"They're places where we keep\nobjects of great value to us,"},{"time":468984,"text":"where we simply treasure them\nfor them being themselves."},{"time":472966,"text":"If someone was to throw\nan egg at the Sistine Chapel,"},{"time":475777,"text":"we'd all go crazy."},{"time":477704,"text":"If someone wanted\nto build a seven-star hotel"},{"time":480194,"text":"at the bottom of the Grand Canyon,"},{"time":482033,"text":"then we would laugh them out of Arizona."},{"time":484494,"text":"Yet every day we dredge, pollute\nand overfish our oceans."},{"time":488927,"text":"And I think it's easier for us to do that,"},{"time":491357,"text":"because when we see the ocean,"},{"time":493477,"text":"we don't see the havoc we're wreaking."},{"time":495429,"text":"Because for most people,"},{"time":497023,"text":"the ocean is like this."},{"time":498980,"text":"And it's really hard"},{"time":500155,"text":"to think of something that's just\nso plain and so enormous, as fragile."},{"time":505597,"text":"It's simply too massive,\ntoo vast, too endless."},{"time":509387,"text":"And what do you see here?"},{"time":510634,"text":"I think most people actually\nlook past to the horizon."},{"time":513713,"text":"So I think there's a real danger"},{"time":515426,"text":"that we never really see the sea,"},{"time":518337,"text":"and if we don't really see it,"},{"time":519870,"text":"if it doesn't have its own iconography,"},{"time":522293,"text":"if we miss its majesty,"},{"time":524329,"text":"then there's a big danger\nthat we take it for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528772,"text":"Cancun is famous for spring break,"},{"time":532113,"text":"tequila and foam parties."},{"time":534396,"text":"And its waters are where frat boys\ncan ride around on Jet Skis"},{"time":537963,"text":"and banana boats."},{"time":539590,"text":"But because of our work there,\nthere's now a little corner of Cancun"},{"time":543627,"text":"that is simply precious for being itself."},{"time":547071,"text":"And we don't want to stop in Grenada,"},{"time":549726,"text":"in Cancun or the Bahamas."},{"time":552496,"text":"Just last month, I installed\nthese Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse"},{"time":556411,"text":"in the Thames River,"},{"time":559062,"text":"in central London, right in front\nof the Houses of Parliament,"},{"time":562588,"text":"putting a stark message\nabout climate change"},{"time":565569,"text":"in front of the people that have\nthe power to help change things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571049,"text":"Because for me, this is just\nthe beginning of the mission."},{"time":574111,"text":"We want to team up with other inventors,"},{"time":576641,"text":"creators, philanthropists,\neducators, biologists,"},{"time":580586,"text":"to see better futures for our oceans."},{"time":582984,"text":"And we want to see beyond sculpture,"},{"time":585556,"text":"beyond art, even."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587995,"text":"Say you're a 14-year-old kid from the city,"},{"time":590437,"text":"and you've never seen the ocean."},{"time":592476,"text":"And instead of getting taken\nto the natural history museum"},{"time":596093,"text":"or an aquarium,"},{"time":597705,"text":"you get taken out to the ocean,"},{"time":600251,"text":"to an underwater Noah's Ark,"},{"time":603036,"text":"which you can access\nthrough a dry-glass viewing tunnel,"},{"time":607030,"text":"where you can see\nall the wildlife of the land"},{"time":609456,"text":"be colonized by the wildlife of the ocean."},{"time":612290,"text":"Clearly, it would blow your mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615290,"text":"So let's think big and let's think deep."},{"time":618569,"text":"Who knows where our imagination\nand willpower can lead us?"},{"time":622029,"text":"I hope that by bringing\nour art into the ocean,"},{"time":625001,"text":"that not only do we take advantage\nof amazing creativity"},{"time":628554,"text":"and visual impact of the setting,"},{"time":630713,"text":"but that we are also\ngiving something back,"},{"time":633183,"text":"and by encouraging\nnew environments to thrive,"},{"time":636565,"text":"and in some way opening up a new --\nor maybe it's a really old way"},{"time":641658,"text":"of seeing the seas:"},{"time":643749,"text":"as delicate, precious places,"},{"time":647303,"text":"worthy of our protection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649896,"text":"Our oceans are sacred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651675,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}